	4 <a href="javascript:card_browser(319)">Orc Ambusher</a><br>
	2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(154)">Orc Inquisitor</a><br>
	2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(156)">Orc Soldier</a><br>
	1 <a href="javascript:card_browser(147)">Morgul Warden</a> (R)<br>
	1 Orc Warrior<br>
    Conditions:<br>
	2 Uruk-hai <a href="javascript:card_browser(303)">Armor</a>y<br>
	2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(37)">Their Arrows Enrage</a><br>
	1 <a href="javascript:card_browser(953)">Wizard Storm</a><br>
	2 <a href="javascript:card_browser(321)">Under the Watching Eye</a><br>
	1 Desperate Defence of the Ring (R)<br>
    Events:<br>
	3 <a href="javascript:card_browser(19)">Bred for Battle</a><br>
	1 One of You Must Do This<br>
	1 The Dark Lord Advances<br>
	1 Massing the East<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> In the bidding it is not very wise to bet more than 5 tokens, because the Ring will be used quite a couple of times. As you can see below, the fellowship is pretty straightforward and gets built up pretty early in the game. Well, the first sneaky steps on the adventure path are covered by occasional Legolas arrows, but before heading towards underground sites, Boromir or any of the two dwarves should be already in the play securing the path to the next sanctuary. In general, do not worry too much about loosing a companion or two before the last sites  all companions are assumed to be on berserk mood, not caring about themselves, and annihilating the minions till the last breath. Just one more thing about the fellowship, if trying to catch up with your opponent, changing the ring-bearer to Sam is quite likely to happen. The same goes for hobbit swords  try to share two between three.<br>
<br>
Now, lets look at the shadow side. The idea here is to have constantly a significant amount of wounds on the opponents companions. While his mind should already be troubled by it, the additional draw and hand deck discards will add some oil to the fire. In my opinion, the juiciest part of this deck is the adventure path  it is so offensive, that every step is a sheer torture. Anyways, to have a slowly moving opponent is quite probable and if you are lucky, the movement could become as slow as zero in later stages &#61514; <br>
<br>
Thanks and I hope you enjoyed it like I have!<br>
